aglClipBufferRect Read Me

This example shows the use of clip regions and buffer rects in AGL.

The example has menu operations to create a standard or model window and then toggle clip regions and buffer rects on and off.  Note the controls correct receive clicks and the window resize is properly supported.

See Technical Q&A 1222 at <http://developer.apple.com/qa> for more details.

This example also provides a single Mach-O source and both CodeWarrior 8.3+
and Project Builder projects, showing how each should be structured.
